      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PITMAN GO WELL (1) comes into this as a quickest on the card winner last time at this track, scoring by one length (22.25). With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Expected to be in this for a long way. TARAWI QUEENIE (7) filled a minor placing last start at The Gardens behind Kalani Sea (23.31) in a Grade 5. Turned chasing the leaders but kept coming. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Can feature again. GRAND ARTIST (2) turned in a better effort at Richmond last start, finishing third behind Melania Banner (23.08) in a Grade 5. Chased the leaders and with a clean run can be prominent. Can measure up. MY HARLEY (5) has been in the placings at his last two runs, most recently when third (22.45) in a Grade 5 over 388m at this track. Good beginner who will be prominent from trap seven.",
